        {
          "text": "√(a − b) = √a − √b",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "The product property states √(a · b) = √a · √b when a ≥ 0 and b ≥ 0. This is the key property used to simplify radicals by separating perfect square factors."
    },
